  "difficulty": "Medium",
  "tags": [
    "Linked List",
    "Two Pointers"
  ],
  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Remove Nth Node From End of List\n\nRemove the `n`th node counted from the end of a singly linked list and return the new head.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: head = [9,8,7,6], n = 2\nOutput: [9,8,6]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: head = [4], n = 1\nOutput: []\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: head = [1,2,3], n = 3\nOutput: [2,3]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- The judge provides a `ListNode` class with `val` and `next` fields.\n- Node values fit in normal signed integer range.\n- The total number of nodes across one test case is kept small enough for local execution.\n- `1 <= n <= length of the list`",
  "editorial": "Place a dummy node before the head. Move a fast pointer `n + 1` steps from the dummy, then advance both pointers until fast reaches the end.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def removeNthFromEnd(self, head, n):\n        dummy = ListNode(0, head)\n        fast = slow = dummy\n        for _ in range(n + 1):\n            fast = fast.next\n        while fast:\n            fast = fast.next\n            slow = slow.next\n        slow.next = slow.next.next\n        return dummy.next\n```",
  "hints": [
    "A dummy node handles deleting the original head.",
    "Keep a fixed gap between two pointers."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def removeNthFromEnd(self, head, n):\n        pass\n"
  },
  "entrypoint": {
    "class_name": "Solution",
    "method_name": "removeNthFromEnd"
  },
